pull_request.title: subversion: remove java bindings
pull_request.body:
A problem that is encountered in bottling is that we have some formulas that require `subversion` to fetch the source, and `subversion` has been made dependent on `openjdk`, which is a beast and often broken for new macOS releases.

Originally, subversion only had an option for the java bindings, and somewhere along the way it was made a build dependency. But it is annoying, and not core to its functionality. I’d like to propose that we remove this dependency. Especially since the formula is used by Homebrew itself.

If there is user demand, we could add the bindings in a separate formula.

pull_request.title: subversion: remove java bindings
pull_request.body:
A problem that is encountered in bottling is that we have some formulas that require `subversion` to fetch the source, and `subversion` has been made dependent on `openjdk`, which is a beast and often broken for new macOS releases.

Originally, subversion only had an option for the java bindings, and somewhere along the way it was made a build dependency. But it is annoying, and not core to its functionality. I’d like to propose that we remove this dependency. Especially since the formula is used by Homebrew itself.

If there is user demand, we could add the bindings in a separate formula.

pull_request.title: subversion: remove java bindings
pull_request.body:
A problem that is encountered in bottling is that we have some formulas that require `subversion` to fetch the source, and `subversion` has been made dependent on `openjdk`, which is a beast and often broken for new macOS releases.

Originally, subversion only had an option for the java bindings, and somewhere along the way it was made a build dependency. But it is annoying, and not core to its functionality. I’d like to propose that we remove this dependency. Especially since the formula is used by Homebrew itself.

If there is user demand, we could add the bindings in a separate formula.
